<item>
            <title>[LU-18848] symlink permission issue when sticky bit set on directory</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18848</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We ran into a strange issue when the sticky bit is set on a directory and the directory is owned by root.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Symlinks owned by non root users in that directory give permission denied when trying to open the symlink.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mkdir /lustre_mnt/testdir&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;chmod 1777 /lustre_mnt/testdir&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;chown root:root /lustre_mnt/testdir (if the mkdir wasn&apos;t done as root)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Now as a non root user&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cd /lustre_mnt/testdir&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;touch testfile&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ln -s testfile testlink&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cat testlink - this works as the user&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) As root, try to cat testlink:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; cat testlink&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cat: testlink: Permission denied&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; cat testfile&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cat of testfile worked, but not the symlink.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4) Change permissions on /lustre_mnt/testdir to 777&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;chmod 777 /lustre_mnt/testdir&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now the cat of testlink works as root&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;5) Change permissions on /lustre_mnt/testdir to 1777&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;chmod 1777 /lustre_mnt/testdir&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now the cat of testlink gives permission denied&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like the directory must be owned by root for this to happen.&#160; &#160;We were confused by this behavior and weren&apos;t sure if it&apos;s a bug?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
